Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    LightLocalizer
    The LightLocalizer class performs small corrections to the trajectory of the robot at line intersections to ensure that it moves in a straight line.
    Main
    This class controls the execution of the different steps required for a robot to autonomously go rescue a stranded vehicle.
    Mapping
    The Mapping class converts raw map data to coordinates that are used by the robot after initial localization.
    Navigation
    The navigation class allows for the robot's movement along a given path.
    ObstacleAvoidance
    The ObstacleAvoidance class detects and identifies obstacles near the robot.
    Odometer
    The odometer class keeps track of the robot's (x, y, theta) position.
    Resources
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase.
    Search
    The search class enables the robot to search for the car in the search zone.
    UltrasonicLocalizer
    The UltrasoniocLocalizer class executes the initial localization of the robot.
    Utility
    The Class Utility includes shared utility methods to avoid cluttering in other classes.
